Eastern Cape businessman Bongile Nkola will get another shot at setting aside a high court ruling that two of his properties should be sold off to settle a longstanding debt he owes a steel company. He has been granted leave to take the matter on appeal to the Supreme Court of Appeal (SCA).For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions.&nbsp;&nbsp;